div.p:

                  Quest. 
                But now a question will grow from hence;




May not a wicked man that never was truly broken-hearted make a large and open confession of his sinnes?

So from hence the doctrine is this,
                  Doctrine:
                The soule that is truly pierced for sinne, is carried against it with a restlesse dislike and distaste of it: or thus, Sound contrition of heart, ever brings a thorow detestation of sinne; this they professedly proclaime before the Apostles. As if they had said thus much in more words;
